Document: Projection
Path: godot/classes/class_projection.rst
Summary: This section describes the individual vector components (w, x, y, z) that make up the Projection matrix.

Properties:
*   w (Vector4): The projection matrix's W vector (column 3). Equivalent to array index `3`. Default: Vector4(0, 0, 0, 1)
*   x (Vector4): The projection matrix's X vector (column 0). Equivalent to array index `0`. Default: Vector4(1, 0, 0, 0)
*   y (Vector4): The projection matrix's Y vector (column 1). Equivalent to array index `1`. Default: Vector4(0, 1, 0, 0)
*   z (Vector4): The projection matrix's Z vector (column 2). Equivalent to array index `2`. Default: Vector4(0, 0, 1, 0)
---CHUNK---
Document: Projection
Path: godot/classes/class_projection.rst
Summary: This section details the constructors, methods, and operators available for the Projection class, used for 3D projection transformations.

Constructor Descriptions:
Projection()
Constructs a default-initialized Projection identical to IDENTITY. Note: In C#, this constructs a Projection identical to ZERO.
Projection(from: Projection)
Constructs a Projection as a copy of the given Projection.
Projection(from: Transform3D)
Constructs a Projection as a copy of the given Transform3D.
Projection(x_axis: Vector4, y_axis: Vector4, z_axis: Vector4, w_axis: Vector4)
Constructs a Projection from four Vector4 values (matrix columns).

Method Descriptions:
Method: create_depth_correction(flip_y: bool) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new Projection for depth correction, mapping positions from -1 to 1 range to 0 to 1, and vertically flipping based on `flip_y`.
Method: create_fit_aabb(aabb: AABB) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new Projection that scales a given projection to fit around an AABB in projection space.
Method: create_for_hmd(eye: int, aspect: float, intraocular_dist: float, display_width: float, display_to_lens: float, oversample: float, z_near: float, z_far: float) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new Projection for head-mounted displays with specified aspect ratio, eye distance, display parameters, and clipping planes. `eye` specifies left (1) or right (2) eye.
Method: create_frustum(left: float, right: float, bottom: float, top: float, z_near: float, z_far: float) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new frustum Projection with the given clipping planes.
Method: create_frustum_aspect(size: float, aspect: float, offset: Vector2, z_near: float, z_far: float, flip_fov: bool = false) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new frustum Projection with specified size, aspect ratio, offset, and clipping planes. `flip_fov` determines if the field of view is flipped.
Method: create_light_atlas_rect(rect: Rect2) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new Projection that projects positions into the given Rect2.
Method: create_orthogonal(left: float, right: float, bottom: float, top: float, z_near: float, z_far: float) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new orthogonal Projection with the given clipping planes.
Method: create_orthogonal_aspect(size: float, aspect: float, z_near: float, z_far: float, flip_fov: bool = false) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new orthogonal Projection with specified size, aspect ratio, and clipping planes. `flip_fov` determines if the field of view is flipped.
Method: create_perspective(fovy: float, aspect: float, z_near: float, z_far: float, flip_fov: bool = false) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new perspective Projection with specified Y-axis field of view (degrees), aspect ratio, and clipping planes. `flip_fov` determines if the field of view is flipped.
Method: create_perspective_hmd(fovy: float, aspect: float, z_near: float, z_far: float, flip_fov: bool, eye: int, intraocular_dist: float, convergence_dist: float) -> Projection (static)
Creates a new perspective Projection for head-mounted displays with specified Y-axis field of view, aspect ratio, clipping distances, eye distance, and convergence distance. `eye` specifies left (1) or right (2) eye. `flip_fov` determines if the field of view is flipped.
Method: determinant() -> float (const)
Returns a scalar value that is the signed factor by which areas are scaled by this matrix. If the sign is negative, the matrix flips the orientation of the area. The determinant can be used to calculate the invertibility of a matrix or solve linear systems of equations involving the matrix, among other applications.
Method: flipped_y() -> Projection (const)
Returns a copy of this Projection with the signs of the values of the Y column flipped.
Method: get_aspect() -> float (const)
Returns the X:Y aspect ratio of this Projection's viewport.
Method: get_far_plane_half_extents() -> Vector2 (const)
Returns the dimensions of the far clipping plane of the projection, divided by two.
Method: get_fov() -> float (const)
Returns the horizontal field of view of the projection (in degrees).
Method: get_fovy(fovx: float, aspect: float) -> float (static)
Returns the vertical field of view of the projection (in degrees) associated with the given horizontal field of view (in degrees) and aspect ratio. Note: Unlike most methods of Projection, `aspect` is expected to be 1 divided by the X:Y aspect ratio.
Method: get_lod_multiplier() -> float (const)
Returns the factor by which the visible level of detail is scaled by this Projection.
Method: get_pixels_per_meter(for_pixel_width: int) -> int (const)
Returns `for_pixel_width` divided by the viewport's width measured in meters on the near plane, after this Projection is applied.
Method: get_projection_plane(plane: int) -> Plane (const)
Returns the clipping plane of this Projection whose index is given by `plane`. `plane` should be equal to one of PLANE_NEAR, PLANE_FAR, PLANE_LEFT, PLANE_TOP, PLANE_RIGHT, or PLANE_BOTTOM.
Method: get_viewport_half_extents() -> Vector2 (const)
Returns the dimensions of the viewport plane that this Projection projects positions onto, divided by two.
Method: get_z_far() -> float (const)
Returns the distance for this Projection beyond which positions are clipped.
Method: get_z_near() -> float (const)
Returns the distance for this Projection before which positions are clipped.
Method: inverse() -> Projection (const)
Returns a Projection that performs the inverse of this Projection's projective transformation.
Method: is_orthogonal() -> bool (const)
Returns `true` if this Projection performs an orthogonal projection.
Method: jitter_offseted(offset: Vector2) -> Projection (const)
Returns a Projection with the X and Y values from the given Vector2 added to the first and second values of the final column respectively.
Method: perspective_znear_adjusted(new_znear: float) -> Projection (const)
Returns a Projection with the near clipping distance adjusted to be `new_znear`. Note: The original Projection must be a perspective projection.

Operator Descriptions:
Operator: !=(right: Projection) -> bool
Returns `true` if the projections are not equal. Key Rule: Due to floating-point precision errors, this may return `true`, even if the projections are virtually equal. An `is_equal_approx` method may be added in a future version of Godot.
Operator: *(right: Projection) -> Projection
Returns a Projection that applies the combined transformations of this Projection and `right`.
Operator: *(right: Vector4) -> Vector4
Projects (multiplies) the given Vector4 by this Projection matrix.
Operator: ==(right: Projection) -> bool
Returns `true` if the projections are equal. Key Rule: Due to floating-point precision errors, this may return `false`, even if the projections are virtually equal. An `is_equal_approx` method may be added in a future version of Godot.
Operator: [](index: int) -> Vector4
Returns the column of the Projection with the given index. Indices are in the following order: x, y, z, w.